The paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically the problem of detecting camouflaged moving foreground objects. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category. Additionally, the paper uses wavelet transforms, which are commonly used in signal processing and image analysis, suggesting that the paper could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Information Theory (cs.IT) categories. The paper also uses statistical models to estimate the likelihood of foreground and background in different wavelet bands, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories.
